se.hig.aod.lab2

Class LinkedList<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • se.hig.aod.lab2.LinkedList<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - type to store
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<T>, ExtendedList<T>, List<T>

    public class LinkedList<T>
extends java.lang.Object
implements ExtendedList<T>, java.lang.Iterable<T>
    A double-linked list

    For-each iteration available
    Example: 
     
  for(T element : list)
      System.out.println(element);
    Author:
    Viktor Hanstorp (ndi14vhp@student.hig.se)

    • Nested Class Summary

      Nested Classes 
      Modifier and Type Class and Description
      class  LinkedList.Element
      Wrapper for a ListNode that only expose the data it is holding and a remove function
      class  LinkedList.SearchResult
      Results from a search operation on the list

      Found elements are in wrappers in the results

      It is possible to remove found elements by calling remove on the wrapper, or remove on this LinkedList.SearchResult to remove all findings from the list

      For examples see search(Object)

      • search

        public LinkedList.SearchResult search(T element)
        Search for an element in the list

        Example: Removing all 'g' characters from the list by using search 
         
  linkedList.search('g').remove();
        Example: Count instances of character 'a' 
         
  int count = linkedList.search('a').getSize();
        Example: Check if the list contains 'b' 
         
  boolean containsB = !linkedList.search('b').isEmpty();
        Example: Iterate over results 
         
  for(LinkedList <Integer>.Element element : testList.search(1000))
  {
      System.out.println(element);
  }
        Parameters:
        element - the element to search for
        Returns:
        a LinkedList.SearchResult with the found elements
